Got it! Let's create a simple Angular project using AG Grid from scratch.

Step 1: Create a new Angular project
If you don't have the Angular CLI installed, install it by running:

bash
Copy code
npm install -g @angular/cli
Now, create a new Angular project:

bash
Copy code
ng new ag-grid-demo
cd ag-grid-demo
Step 2: Install AG Grid
Inside the project directory, install the ag-grid-angular package:

bash
Copy code
npm install ag-grid-angular ag-grid-community
Step 3: Set up AG Grid in Angular
We will now integrate AG Grid into your project.

src/app/app.module.ts
Make sure to import AgGridModule in your AppModule.

typescript
Copy code
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { AppComponent } from './app.component';
import { AgGridModule } from 'ag-grid-angular';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [AppComponent],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    AgGridModule.withComponents([]), // Import AG Grid Module
  ],
  providers: [],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent],
})
export class AppModule {}
src/app/app.component.ts
Now, let's create a component with AG Grid. Weâ€™ll define column headers and sample row data for this example.

typescript
Copy code
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'],
})
export class AppComponent {
  columnDefs = [
    { headerName: 'Make', field: 'make' },
    { headerName: 'Model', field: 'model' },
    { headerName: 'Price', field: 'price' },
  ];

  rowData = [
    { make: 'Toyota', model: 'Celica', price: 35000 },
    { make: 'Ford', model: 'Mondeo', price: 32000 },
    { make: 'Porsche', model: 'Boxster', price: 72000 },
  ];
}
src/app/app.component.html
This is the HTML template where the AG Grid table is displayed.

html
Copy code
<h1>AG Grid Example</h1>
<ag-grid-angular
  style="width: 100%; height: 500px;"
  class="ag-theme-alpine"
  [rowData]="rowData"
  [columnDefs]="columnDefs"
  rowSelection="multiple"
  [animateRows]="true"
></ag-grid-angular>
src/app/app.component.css
You can add some basic styling or leave it empty for now.

css
Copy code
/* Optional custom styles */
Step 4: Run the project
Once everything is set up, you can run your Angular project:

bash
Copy code
ng serve
